1
00:00:01,041 --> 00:00:05,083
[upbeat theme music plays]

2
00:00:05,166 --> 00:00:07,333
<i>♪ You never do know</i>
<i>what's around the bend ♪</i>

3
00:00:07,416 --> 00:00:09,250
<i>♪ Big adventure</i>
<i>or a brand-new friend ♪</i>

4
00:00:09,333 --> 00:00:10,916
<i>♪ When you're curious ♪</i>

5
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:13,791
<i>-♪ Like Curious George ♪</i>
-[chorus] Swing!

6
00:00:13,875 --> 00:00:15,833
<i>-♪ Well, now, every day ♪</i>
-[chorus]<i> ♪ Every day ♪</i>

7
00:00:15,916 --> 00:00:17,791
<i>-♪ Is so glorious ♪</i>
-[chorus]<i> ♪ Glorious ♪</i>

8
00:00:17,875 --> 00:00:19,416
-George.
-<i>♪ And everything ♪</i>

9
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:20,333
[chorus]<i> ♪ Everything ♪</i>

10
00:00:20,416 --> 00:00:22,625
<i>-♪ Is so wondrous ♪</i>
-[chorus]<i> ♪ Wondrous ♪</i>

11
00:00:22,708 --> 00:00:26,791
<i>♪ There's more to explore</i>
<i>when you open your door ♪</i>

12
00:00:26,875 --> 00:00:28,375
<i>♪ And meet friends like this ♪</i>

13
00:00:28,458 --> 00:00:31,416
<i>-♪ You just can't miss ♪</i>
-[chorus] Whoa!

14
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:33,541
<i>-♪ I get curious ♪</i>
-[chorus]<i> ♪ Curious ♪</i>

15
00:00:33,625 --> 00:00:35,791
<i>-♪ And that's marvelous ♪</i>
-[chorus]<i> ♪ Marvelous ♪</i>

16
00:00:35,875 --> 00:00:37,916
<i>♪ And that's your reward ♪</i>

17
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:39,916
<i>♪ You'll never be bored ♪</i>

18
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,416
<i>♪ If you ask yourself,</i>
<i>"What is this?" ♪</i>

19
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,416
<i>♪ Like Curious ♪</i>

20
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:48,375
<i>♪ Like Curious,</i>
<i>Curious George ♪</i>

21
00:00:48,458 --> 00:00:49,458
Oh.

22
00:00:50,791 --> 00:00:53,750
[upbeat ragtime music]

23
00:00:53,833 --> 00:00:56,791
<i>♪♪</i>

24
00:00:56,875 --> 00:00:59,500
[narrator] <i>Little monkeys</i>
<i>love riding buses!</i>

25
00:01:00,875 --> 00:01:04,250
<i>But a ride on the Z bus</i>
<i>was the best trip of all.</i>

26
00:01:04,333 --> 00:01:05,958
[chattering happily]

27
00:01:06,041 --> 00:01:08,000
[narrator]
<i>Because it ended at...</i>

28
00:01:08,083 --> 00:01:10,833
Welcome to Zany Island!

29
00:01:10,916 --> 00:01:13,250
[chattering excitedly]

30
00:01:14,625 --> 00:01:17,416
Say hello
to our new friends, Petey.

31
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:19,541
-Hello.
-[caws]

32
00:01:19,625 --> 00:01:22,416
How would you like
your own Petey?

33
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:25,666
[chattering appreciatively]

34
00:01:25,750 --> 00:01:28,666
Wow!
Nice, George!

35
00:01:28,750 --> 00:01:30,625
Thar be adventure ahead.

36
00:01:30,708 --> 00:01:34,291
And here's a map
to keep ya on course.

37
00:01:34,375 --> 00:01:36,625
[chattering excitedly]

38
00:01:36,708 --> 00:01:39,333
[caws] Have fun.

39
00:01:39,416 --> 00:01:40,833
[grunts appreciatively]

40
00:01:40,916 --> 00:01:42,833
[narrator] <i>George planned</i>
<i>on having a great time.</i>

41
00:01:42,916 --> 00:01:45,041
[chattering happily]

42
00:01:45,125 --> 00:01:46,958
[narrator]
<i>And thanks to his map,</i>

43
00:01:47,041 --> 00:01:48,958
<i>he wouldn't miss a thing.</i>

44
00:01:52,541 --> 00:01:55,500
[exciting music]

45
00:01:55,583 --> 00:01:58,583
-[chattering exhilaratingly]
-[yelling]

46
00:01:59,958 --> 00:02:02,708
[narrator] <i>George and</i>
<i>his friend rode fast rides...</i>

47
00:02:02,791 --> 00:02:04,708
[toads croaking]

48
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:07,375
Slow rides...

49
00:02:07,458 --> 00:02:10,291
[both yelling]

50
00:02:10,375 --> 00:02:11,833
Scary rides...

51
00:02:15,166 --> 00:02:16,000
[both laughing]

52
00:02:16,083 --> 00:02:17,875
Wet rides...

53
00:02:17,958 --> 00:02:20,500
[relaxed music]

54
00:02:20,583 --> 00:02:23,666
And scenic rides...

55
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:26,416
[grunts happily]

56
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,625
[narrator] <i>Until, one by one,</i>

57
00:02:28,708 --> 00:02:30,916
<i>George, Petey, and</i>
<i>the Man with the Yellow Hat</i>

58
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,875
<i>had ridden them all.</i>

59
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:37,666
[upbeat music]

60
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:39,833
Too bad they don't come
in yellow.

61
00:02:39,916 --> 00:02:43,583
<i>♪♪</i>

62
00:02:43,666 --> 00:02:44,875
Lucky you!

63
00:02:44,958 --> 00:02:47,041
You got
the last one in your size.

64
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:49,583
We're usually out of stock
by this time of day.

65
00:02:49,666 --> 00:02:52,458
[grunts appreciatively]

66
00:02:52,541 --> 00:02:58,958
<i>♪♪</i>

67
00:02:59,041 --> 00:03:00,833
-[cannon blasts]
-[gasps]

68
00:03:00,916 --> 00:03:03,000
[grunts excitedly]

69
00:03:03,083 --> 00:03:05,041
[Captain Zany] <i>Avast, mateys!</i>

70
00:03:05,125 --> 00:03:07,541
<i>That be yer warning shot!</i>

71
00:03:07,625 --> 00:03:11,875
<i>Zany Island be closing</i>
<i>in 30 minutes I say.</i>

72
00:03:11,958 --> 00:03:13,416
One more ride?

73
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:15,000
[grunting happily]

74
00:03:16,541 --> 00:03:19,458
[light music]

75
00:03:19,541 --> 00:03:26,541
<i>♪♪</i>

76
00:03:30,541 --> 00:03:32,500
[straining]

77
00:03:32,583 --> 00:03:35,375
[chattering drowsily]

78
00:03:36,083 --> 00:03:38,458
So, did you have
a good time today, George?

79
00:03:38,541 --> 00:03:42,000
[chattering, yawns]

80
00:03:42,083 --> 00:03:44,458
What was your favorite part?

81
00:03:44,541 --> 00:03:47,083
[cawing, chattering]

82
00:03:47,166 --> 00:03:48,625
[laughs]

83
00:03:48,708 --> 00:03:50,791
Yeah, you sure
had fun with Petey.

84
00:03:50,875 --> 00:03:53,416
[light piano music]

85
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:55,833
[yawns]

86
00:03:55,916 --> 00:03:57,458
Huh?

87
00:03:57,541 --> 00:03:58,666
[gasps]

88
00:03:58,750 --> 00:04:00,166
Hey, um...

89
00:04:00,250 --> 00:04:03,041
Where is Petey?
Did we leave him behind?

90
00:04:03,125 --> 00:04:05,416
[grunting in alarm]

91
00:04:07,875 --> 00:04:11,125
[panicked chattering]

92
00:04:12,791 --> 00:04:16,000
Whoa, George, hang on!
I...

93
00:04:16,083 --> 00:04:17,916
Look, I know you're
worried about Petey.

94
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,666
[grunts fearfully]

95
00:04:19,750 --> 00:04:22,500
But it's really late.
I promise,

96
00:04:22,583 --> 00:04:25,458
we'll look for him first thing
in the morning, okay?

97
00:04:26,666 --> 00:04:28,875
[grunts obligingly]

98
00:04:33,625 --> 00:04:35,750
[sighs impatiently]

99
00:04:35,833 --> 00:04:38,708
[narrator]<i> But George didn't</i>
<i>want to wait until morning.</i>

100
00:04:39,958 --> 00:04:41,458
[chatters happily]

101
00:04:41,541 --> 00:04:43,541
[narrator] <i>Luckily,</i>
<i>he didn't have to.</i>

102
00:04:43,625 --> 00:04:45,500
<i>The Z bus ran all night.</i>

103
00:04:45,583 --> 00:04:46,750
[upbeat piano music]

104
00:04:46,833 --> 00:04:49,500
[grunts excitedly]

105
00:04:49,583 --> 00:04:51,791
[narrator]<i> He could rescue</i>
<i>Petey now.</i>

106
00:04:51,875 --> 00:04:57,875
<i>♪♪</i>

107
00:04:57,958 --> 00:05:00,750
[chattering happily]

108
00:05:00,833 --> 00:05:03,041
[narrator] <i>Zany Island</i>
<i>was a big place.</i>

109
00:05:03,125 --> 00:05:05,166
<i>Good thing George</i>
<i>had kept his map.</i>

110
00:05:05,250 --> 00:05:09,166
<i>It showed everywhere</i>
<i>he and Petey had been that day.</i>

111
00:05:10,958 --> 00:05:12,833
[grunts dejectedly]

112
00:05:13,916 --> 00:05:16,875
[chatters in exertion]

113
00:05:16,958 --> 00:05:20,250
[narrator] <i>Let the hunt</i>
<i>for Parrot Petey begin.</i>

114
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:23,000
<i>But George wondered</i>
<i>where to look first?</i>

115
00:05:23,083 --> 00:05:24,791
[grunts hesitatingly]

116
00:05:24,875 --> 00:05:28,000
[narrator] <i>Maybe right here.</i>

117
00:05:28,083 --> 00:05:31,166
<i>The store where George</i>
<i>had gotten his pirate hat!</i>

118
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:34,250
[chatters curiously]

119
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:36,000
[narrator]<i> Those shelves</i>
<i>had been empty,</i>

120
00:05:36,083 --> 00:05:38,583
<i>and those tables</i>
<i>had been messy.</i>

121
00:05:38,666 --> 00:05:41,958
[quiet piano music]

122
00:05:42,041 --> 00:05:43,833
[chatters in surprise]

123
00:05:43,916 --> 00:05:45,583
[chattering excitedly]

124
00:05:45,666 --> 00:05:47,750
[narrator] <i>Maybe this was</i>
<i>where they put all the toys</i>

125
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:50,125
<i>children left behind! </i>

126
00:05:54,083 --> 00:05:56,083
-[chatters amiably]
-[gasps]

127
00:05:56,166 --> 00:05:58,958
[laughing] Whoa!
You're a real monkey.

128
00:05:59,041 --> 00:06:01,583
And an awfully cute one too.

129
00:06:01,666 --> 00:06:03,250
What are you doing up there?

130
00:06:03,333 --> 00:06:06,875
[chatters, caws]

131
00:06:06,958 --> 00:06:10,208
Oh, you're looking for
your lost Parrot Petey, huh?

132
00:06:10,291 --> 00:06:12,000
[chatters agreeably]

133
00:06:12,083 --> 00:06:16,125
Well, we only have
new toys here.

134
00:06:16,208 --> 00:06:20,208
But it might be somewhere
behind all those boxes.

135
00:06:20,291 --> 00:06:24,125
I'll help you look
once I'm done restocking.

136
00:06:24,208 --> 00:06:26,041
[grunts excitedly]

137
00:06:26,125 --> 00:06:29,958
[chatters in exertion]

138
00:06:30,041 --> 00:06:32,291
Which may happen
in record time

139
00:06:32,375 --> 00:06:34,083
if you're helping out!

140
00:06:34,166 --> 00:06:37,125
[lively piano music]

141
00:06:37,208 --> 00:06:44,208
<i>♪♪</i>

142
00:06:50,041 --> 00:06:51,958
[grunts triumphantly]

143
00:06:57,166 --> 00:06:59,875
Sorry we didn't find
your Petey.

144
00:06:59,958 --> 00:07:03,291
[grunts disappointedly]

145
00:07:03,375 --> 00:07:05,625
Let's ask the guys outside.

146
00:07:05,708 --> 00:07:08,166
They go everywhere!

147
00:07:08,250 --> 00:07:09,833
[grunts curiously]

148
00:07:10,875 --> 00:07:11,833
[chatters happily]

149
00:07:11,916 --> 00:07:13,583
[grunts confusedly]

150
00:07:14,208 --> 00:07:17,833
[narrator] <i>Where had</i>
<i>all the confetti gone?</i>

151
00:07:17,916 --> 00:07:21,708
Hey, guys! My friend here
lost a Parrot Petey.

152
00:07:21,791 --> 00:07:23,125
Anybody found one?

153
00:07:23,208 --> 00:07:25,333
Not yet, but it's a big park.

154
00:07:25,416 --> 00:07:27,000
We've got a lot of ground
to cover.

155
00:07:27,083 --> 00:07:28,333
Want to come along?

156
00:07:28,416 --> 00:07:30,666
[chatters agreeably]

157
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:32,041
[grunts in exertion]

158
00:07:32,125 --> 00:07:33,666
Good catch!

159
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:35,708
[light music]

160
00:07:35,791 --> 00:07:37,291
[container whirs]

161
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:39,875
[container whirs]

162
00:07:39,958 --> 00:07:41,333
[chatters curiously]

163
00:07:41,416 --> 00:07:43,666
[narrator]<i> How did everything</i>
<i>from that big bag</i>

164
00:07:43,750 --> 00:07:45,791
<i>fit into that little barrel?</i>

165
00:07:45,875 --> 00:07:48,750
Nice, huh?
The trash cans are fake.

166
00:07:48,833 --> 00:07:51,041
They cover
these underground tubes.

167
00:07:51,125 --> 00:07:53,916
[grunt echoes]

168
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,875
They're like
big vacuum cleaners!

169
00:07:55,958 --> 00:07:59,083
The trash gets sucked down
to a central collection area.

170
00:07:59,166 --> 00:08:01,250
[grunts in awe]

171
00:08:02,875 --> 00:08:04,750
That way, trash collectors
don't disturb

172
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:07,416
our guests during the day.

173
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:09,416
Ready to roll?

174
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:12,250
[chatters agreeably]

175
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:15,000
I hope you find your Petey.

176
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,125
[grunts happily]

177
00:08:21,208 --> 00:08:22,916
[chatters dejectedly]

178
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:25,333
[narrator] <i>But Petey</i>
<i>wasn't to be found.</i>

179
00:08:25,416 --> 00:08:27,250
<i>At least not on the streets.</i>

180
00:08:28,208 --> 00:08:29,083
[grunts inquisitively]

181
00:08:29,166 --> 00:08:31,916
[narrator] <i>It was time</i>
<i>for George to search the rides.</i>

182
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,750
<i>First up,</i>
<i>the roller coaster.</i>

183
00:08:34,832 --> 00:08:36,916
[wheels screeching]

184
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,750
[chatters aggravatingly]

185
00:08:39,832 --> 00:08:41,332
[narrator] <i>George hadn't</i>
<i>remembered the coaster</i>

186
00:08:41,416 --> 00:08:43,332
<i>being that noisy before.</i>

187
00:08:44,833 --> 00:08:47,958
Well, hi, little fella.
What are you doing here?

188
00:08:48,041 --> 00:08:50,250
[chatters, cawing]

189
00:08:50,333 --> 00:08:52,125
[chatters sadly]

190
00:08:52,208 --> 00:08:54,250
You lost your Parrot Petey?

191
00:08:54,333 --> 00:08:55,958
[chatters agreeably]

192
00:08:56,041 --> 00:08:58,208
That's tough.
[grunts]

193
00:08:58,291 --> 00:09:01,791
So's oiling the far wheels
on this coaster.

194
00:09:03,166 --> 00:09:05,375
[chattering excitedly]

195
00:09:05,458 --> 00:09:08,125
[upbeat music]

196
00:09:08,208 --> 00:09:10,916
Hey!
Be careful!

197
00:09:11,916 --> 00:09:14,166
[grunting happily]

198
00:09:14,250 --> 00:09:16,458
Wish I could do that!

199
00:09:16,541 --> 00:09:18,833
[chatters amiably]

200
00:09:18,916 --> 00:09:21,125
Tell you what.
You oil that side.

201
00:09:21,208 --> 00:09:22,875
I'll oil this side.

202
00:09:22,958 --> 00:09:25,166
Then we can search the cars
for your Petey together!

203
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:27,291
[chatters in agreement]

204
00:09:27,375 --> 00:09:31,250
<i>♪♪</i>

205
00:09:31,333 --> 00:09:33,000
[chatters curiously]

206
00:09:33,083 --> 00:09:36,916
<i>♪♪</i>

207
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:38,250
[chatters curiously]

208
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:40,958
Found nothing at this end.

209
00:09:41,041 --> 00:09:42,791
How about you?

210
00:09:45,291 --> 00:09:47,500
[chatters dejectedly]

211
00:09:47,583 --> 00:09:50,416
[grunts inquisitively]

212
00:09:52,375 --> 00:09:56,000
What's this? A map of all
the places you went today?

213
00:09:56,083 --> 00:09:58,416
-[grunts in agreement]
-Hmm.

214
00:09:58,500 --> 00:10:01,208
All those rides
need maintenance too!

215
00:10:01,291 --> 00:10:03,791
What do you say
we help each other out?

216
00:10:03,875 --> 00:10:06,958
[chattering agreeably]

217
00:10:09,083 --> 00:10:10,375
[sighs]

218
00:10:10,458 --> 00:10:13,166
I forgot
the most important part!

219
00:10:13,250 --> 00:10:14,375
[chatters curiously]

220
00:10:14,458 --> 00:10:16,125
To take a test ride!

221
00:10:16,208 --> 00:10:17,541
Think you're up for it?

222
00:10:17,625 --> 00:10:20,541
[chatters excitedly]

223
00:10:23,250 --> 00:10:26,083
[chatters exhilaratingly]

224
00:10:27,291 --> 00:10:29,416
[narrator] <i>There were nuts</i>
<i>to be tightened...</i>

225
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:32,208
[chatters gleefully]

226
00:10:32,291 --> 00:10:35,208
[narrator] <i>Light bulbs</i>
<i>to be changed...</i>

227
00:10:35,291 --> 00:10:38,125
[chatters happily]

228
00:10:38,208 --> 00:10:41,416
[narrator] <i>And cables</i>
<i>to be replaced.</i>

229
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:45,166
[chatters cheerfully]

230
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:47,875
[narrator]<i> But there was</i>
<i>only one more ride to go,</i>

231
00:10:47,958 --> 00:10:50,958
<i>and George still</i>
<i>hadn't found Petey.</i>

232
00:10:51,041 --> 00:10:53,500
Swamp boats, it is.

233
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:58,083
[toads croaking]

234
00:10:58,166 --> 00:11:01,833
[triumphant melody]

235
00:11:01,916 --> 00:11:04,833
[light piano music]

236
00:11:04,916 --> 00:11:07,041
[grunts disappointingly]

237
00:11:07,125 --> 00:11:09,083
[narrator] <i>George had worked</i>
<i>on all the rides</i>

238
00:11:09,166 --> 00:11:10,958
<i>and not found Petey.</i>

239
00:11:11,041 --> 00:11:14,250
-[light tap]
-[gasps, chatters in surprise]

240
00:11:15,958 --> 00:11:19,416
[chattering triumphantly]

241
00:11:21,291 --> 00:11:23,000
[laughs]

242
00:11:23,083 --> 00:11:24,291
Whenever I lose something,

243
00:11:24,375 --> 00:11:27,250
it's usually
in the last place I look!

244
00:11:27,333 --> 00:11:28,916
Ready, George?

245
00:11:29,041 --> 00:11:30,333
[grunts agreeably]

246
00:11:30,416 --> 00:11:31,875
And Petey?

247
00:11:31,958 --> 00:11:34,000
[chatters agreeably]

248
00:11:34,083 --> 00:11:36,541
[light music]

249
00:11:36,625 --> 00:11:39,541
[toads croaking]

250
00:11:39,625 --> 00:11:42,625
<i>♪♪</i>

251
00:11:42,708 --> 00:11:46,125
[birds chirping]

252
00:11:46,208 --> 00:11:48,541
Hey there!
Has anyone seen my monkey?

253
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:50,416
[all shushing]

254
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,375
[chattering drowsily]

255
00:11:53,458 --> 00:11:55,875
[snoring]

256
00:11:59,416 --> 00:12:02,333
[lively piano music]

257
00:12:02,416 --> 00:12:08,125
<i>♪♪</i>

258
00:12:08,208 --> 00:12:10,458
[chattering excitedly]

259
00:12:10,541 --> 00:12:14,166
[narrator]
<i>George loved snowy days.</i>

260
00:12:14,250 --> 00:12:16,166
<i>Wherever he wanted to go,</i>

261
00:12:16,250 --> 00:12:18,125
<i>he could ride his toboggan.</i>

262
00:12:18,208 --> 00:12:21,000
[chatters in fear]

263
00:12:21,083 --> 00:12:23,500
[grunting in alarm]

264
00:12:23,583 --> 00:12:25,208
-[grunts]
-Oh!

265
00:12:25,291 --> 00:12:27,541
Oh, my goodness!

266
00:12:27,625 --> 00:12:29,208
Morning, George.

267
00:12:29,291 --> 00:12:32,125
[chattering amiably]

268
00:12:32,208 --> 00:12:34,083
[grunts in surprise]

269
00:12:35,083 --> 00:12:36,875
[grunts, groans]

270
00:12:42,208 --> 00:12:45,958
George, is that you
inside that snowman?

271
00:12:46,041 --> 00:12:48,375
[shivers, chatters happily]

272
00:12:48,458 --> 00:12:50,583
[grunts amiably]

273
00:12:50,666 --> 00:12:53,375
[chattering inquisitively]

274
00:12:54,208 --> 00:12:56,125
Oh, this?
It's my hockey stick.

275
00:12:56,208 --> 00:12:58,125
I'm on my way to the ice rink.

276
00:12:58,208 --> 00:13:01,000
[chatters curiously]

277
00:13:01,083 --> 00:13:02,583
Sure, try it out!

278
00:13:02,666 --> 00:13:05,166
-[grunts admiringly]
-Whoa!

279
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:06,666
-[chattering happily]
-[laughs]

280
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:09,208
You don't hold it like
a baseball bat, George.

281
00:13:09,291 --> 00:13:12,000
[grunts understandingly]

282
00:13:12,083 --> 00:13:14,416
[playful music]

283
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:15,666
[laughs]

284
00:13:15,750 --> 00:13:17,500
You don't ride it either.

285
00:13:17,583 --> 00:13:20,291
Want me to teach you
how to play?

286
00:13:20,375 --> 00:13:21,958
[chatters agreeably]

287
00:13:22,041 --> 00:13:24,416
Great!
Let's go to the rink.

288
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:27,250
[chattering excitedly]

289
00:13:34,291 --> 00:13:36,708
[chattering curiously]

290
00:13:36,791 --> 00:13:39,375
Oh, that's
the ice-resurfacing machine.

291
00:13:39,458 --> 00:13:42,625
It makes the ice smooth
so you can skate on it.

292
00:13:43,791 --> 00:13:45,625
Hey, boys.

293
00:13:45,708 --> 00:13:47,250
Sorry to tell you this,

294
00:13:47,333 --> 00:13:49,375
but the rink's closed
for a week.

295
00:13:49,458 --> 00:13:51,166
-Aw!
-[chatters dejectedly]

296
00:13:51,250 --> 00:13:53,958
Yeah, the community theater
is rehearsing

297
00:13:54,041 --> 00:13:56,208
for "Goldilocks and
the Three Bears on Ice."

298
00:13:56,291 --> 00:13:57,416
[chuckles]

299
00:13:57,500 --> 00:14:00,416
[light piano music]

300
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:03,208
<i>♪♪</i>

301
00:14:03,291 --> 00:14:05,041
Well, no harm done.

302
00:14:05,125 --> 00:14:06,708
You can use the rink next week.

303
00:14:06,791 --> 00:14:09,166
-[grunts disappointingly]
-Mm.

304
00:14:09,250 --> 00:14:11,500
[grunting]

305
00:14:11,583 --> 00:14:13,666
This tarp's frozen solid!

306
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:16,083
Hey, could you give me a hand?

307
00:14:16,166 --> 00:14:17,625
-[chatters agreeably]
-Sure!

308
00:14:17,708 --> 00:14:20,458
<i>♪♪</i>

309
00:14:20,541 --> 00:14:22,375
[straining]
Whew!

310
00:14:22,458 --> 00:14:23,708
Thanks!

311
00:14:25,708 --> 00:14:27,750
[chatters inquisitively]

312
00:14:27,833 --> 00:14:29,416
[narrator]
<i>The layer of ice on top</i>

313
00:14:29,500 --> 00:14:32,750
<i>made the frozen tarp</i>
<i>look just like...</i>

314
00:14:32,833 --> 00:14:35,166
<i>a little ice rink.</i>

315
00:14:36,833 --> 00:14:40,041
[chattering excitedly]

316
00:14:44,041 --> 00:14:45,541
I don't know, George.

317
00:14:45,625 --> 00:14:48,250
I think that tarp's
a little small to skate on.

318
00:14:48,333 --> 00:14:50,458
[grunts curiously]

319
00:14:51,416 --> 00:14:53,083
[chatters happily]

320
00:14:59,166 --> 00:15:01,291
[chatters inquisitively]

321
00:15:01,375 --> 00:15:03,250
Sure, you can use that.

322
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:04,625
What do you need it for?

323
00:15:04,708 --> 00:15:09,375
[chattering happily]

324
00:15:09,458 --> 00:15:11,375
Ohh!

325
00:15:11,458 --> 00:15:13,708
George wants
to make our own ice rink.

326
00:15:13,791 --> 00:15:16,208
[chattering agreeably]

327
00:15:16,291 --> 00:15:19,041
Hmm.
Sounds like a fun project.

328
00:15:19,125 --> 00:15:21,500
-[grunting cheerfully]
-Yeah!

329
00:15:21,583 --> 00:15:24,500
[upbeat piano music]

330
00:15:24,583 --> 00:15:31,583
<i>♪♪</i>

331
00:15:50,208 --> 00:15:53,166
[water splashing]

332
00:15:53,250 --> 00:15:55,708
Wow!
Looks good, you guys.

333
00:15:55,791 --> 00:15:58,625
It should freeze to ice
by tomorrow morning.

334
00:15:58,708 --> 00:16:02,125
Meanwhile, you two look like
you could use some cocoa.

335
00:16:02,208 --> 00:16:04,208
-[chatters excitedly]
-Yeah!

336
00:16:08,208 --> 00:16:11,250
[wind whistling]

337
00:16:14,416 --> 00:16:16,833
[water freezing, ice cracking]

338
00:16:16,916 --> 00:16:19,416
[shimmering tone]

339
00:16:20,333 --> 00:16:23,416
[chattering happily]

340
00:16:25,416 --> 00:16:27,458
[grunts triumphantly]

341
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:31,333
[chatters fearfully]

342
00:16:31,416 --> 00:16:32,875
[grunts in relief]

343
00:16:32,958 --> 00:16:35,833
Hey, George!

344
00:16:35,916 --> 00:16:38,416
[chuckles]
It worked!

345
00:16:38,500 --> 00:16:40,291
You know, you're pretty good

346
00:16:40,375 --> 00:16:42,333
at building ice rinks,
for a city kid.

347
00:16:42,416 --> 00:16:44,250
[chatters appreciatively]

348
00:16:44,333 --> 00:16:45,875
Let's play hockey!

349
00:16:45,958 --> 00:16:47,333
[grunts excitedly]

350
00:16:47,416 --> 00:16:49,375
[groans]

351
00:16:49,458 --> 00:16:50,708
[chatters gleefully]

352
00:16:51,791 --> 00:16:53,541
Here we go!

353
00:16:53,625 --> 00:16:56,125
[chatters happily]

354
00:16:56,208 --> 00:16:59,333
[scraping]

355
00:16:59,416 --> 00:17:01,291
[chatters in fear]

356
00:17:01,375 --> 00:17:03,833
This is not good!

357
00:17:03,916 --> 00:17:05,750
Whoa!

358
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:07,250
[snow tumbling]

359
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:09,915
[chattering fearfully]

360
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,333
[grunts in alarm]

361
00:17:11,415 --> 00:17:13,250
[thud]

362
00:17:13,333 --> 00:17:14,500
You okay, George?

363
00:17:14,583 --> 00:17:15,875
[grunts agreeably]

364
00:17:20,583 --> 00:17:21,790
Hmm.

365
00:17:27,375 --> 00:17:29,791
That is not supposed
to do that.

366
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:35,583
This ice is a lot lumpier
than at the rink.

367
00:17:36,375 --> 00:17:37,666
[grunts in agreement]

368
00:17:38,750 --> 00:17:40,250
[chatters curiously]

369
00:17:40,333 --> 00:17:42,833
Good question, George.

370
00:17:43,833 --> 00:17:46,375
[tree creaking, wind whistling]

371
00:17:49,416 --> 00:17:51,208
[chatters curiously]

372
00:17:53,250 --> 00:17:55,458
-[grunts happily]
-Ah!

373
00:17:55,541 --> 00:17:58,458
It was really windy last night.

374
00:17:58,541 --> 00:18:00,875
The wind must have made
the water wavy

375
00:18:00,958 --> 00:18:02,625
when it was freezing.

376
00:18:02,708 --> 00:18:05,500
[grunts disappointingly]

377
00:18:05,583 --> 00:18:07,833
We'll never be able
to skate on that.

378
00:18:07,916 --> 00:18:12,375
Guess we'll just have to wait
till the rink opens again.

379
00:18:12,458 --> 00:18:13,625
[grunts curiously]

380
00:18:13,708 --> 00:18:16,500
[chatters excitedly]

381
00:18:16,583 --> 00:18:17,791
What is it, George?

382
00:18:17,875 --> 00:18:19,541
[chatters happily]

383
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:26,375
[grunts in exertion]

384
00:18:26,458 --> 00:18:27,833
[chatters happily]

385
00:18:27,916 --> 00:18:31,416
Oh, yeah!
The ice-resurfacing machine!

386
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:34,750
[chattering excitedly]

387
00:18:37,458 --> 00:18:40,250
Huh. You think
they'd loan it to us?

388
00:18:40,333 --> 00:18:42,583
[chattering curiously]

389
00:18:42,666 --> 00:18:45,333
[cars honking]

390
00:18:45,416 --> 00:18:48,333
[grunts hesitatingly]

391
00:18:48,416 --> 00:18:51,291
[chatters negatively]

392
00:18:51,375 --> 00:18:53,750
[sighs]
Me neither.

393
00:18:54,916 --> 00:18:56,583
[chatters curiously]

394
00:18:59,791 --> 00:19:01,541
[grunts curiously]

395
00:19:05,708 --> 00:19:09,458
[chattering happily]

396
00:19:10,875 --> 00:19:14,541
Yeah, maybe we can make one
if we figure out how it works!

397
00:19:14,625 --> 00:19:16,541
[light piano music]

398
00:19:16,625 --> 00:19:19,500
-Uh, George.
-[chatters inquisitively]

399
00:19:19,583 --> 00:19:22,583
Maybe we should figure it out
someplace else.

400
00:19:22,666 --> 00:19:25,625
[chatters in agreement]

401
00:19:25,708 --> 00:19:27,541
[keyboard clacking]

402
00:19:27,625 --> 00:19:31,750
[grunts understandingly]

403
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:34,291
Okay, I see.

404
00:19:34,375 --> 00:19:36,583
The machine wets down
the surface of the ice

405
00:19:36,666 --> 00:19:38,500
with warm water.

406
00:19:38,583 --> 00:19:42,875
Then this big cloth smooths
the surface before it freezes.

407
00:19:42,958 --> 00:19:45,875
[grunts comprehendingly]

408
00:19:45,958 --> 00:19:48,333
[groans]
We better get to work.

409
00:19:48,416 --> 00:19:50,666
[chatters agreeably]

410
00:19:53,625 --> 00:19:55,083
[narrator] <i>If George and Bill</i>
<i>were going to make</i>

411
00:19:55,166 --> 00:19:57,541
<i>their own</i>
<i>ice-resurfacing machine,</i>

412
00:19:57,625 --> 00:19:59,791
<i>they had to find the parts</i>
<i>they would need.</i>

413
00:19:59,875 --> 00:20:01,541
Let's see.

414
00:20:01,625 --> 00:20:05,000
We need something
to wet down the ice.

415
00:20:05,083 --> 00:20:07,083
Hmm.

416
00:20:09,458 --> 00:20:12,500
[chatters curiously]

417
00:20:14,708 --> 00:20:17,416
I don't know.
It's kind of small.

418
00:20:21,375 --> 00:20:22,916
[grunts excitedly]

419
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:25,583
[chattering happily]

420
00:20:25,666 --> 00:20:28,791
We'd need to put holes
in it to drip water.

421
00:20:28,875 --> 00:20:31,958
[chatters happily]

422
00:20:32,041 --> 00:20:33,583
[light tapping]

423
00:20:33,666 --> 00:20:35,125
That's great!

424
00:20:35,208 --> 00:20:40,125
Then what can we use
to smooth out the surface?

425
00:20:40,208 --> 00:20:41,708
[chatters excitedly]

426
00:20:42,666 --> 00:20:43,791
Perfect!

427
00:20:47,041 --> 00:20:50,041
Now, how do we pull
the tub and doormat?

428
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,666
[chatters triumphantly]

429
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:56,833
[duck winding]

430
00:20:56,916 --> 00:20:59,000
[duck quacking]

431
00:20:59,083 --> 00:21:01,000
[ducks quacking]

432
00:21:01,083 --> 00:21:04,083
[quacking slows, stops]

433
00:21:04,166 --> 00:21:06,458
[grunts disappointedly]

434
00:21:06,541 --> 00:21:08,125
Time to wind them again.

435
00:21:09,833 --> 00:21:11,541
[chatters negatively]

436
00:21:15,041 --> 00:21:17,625
[chatters triumphantly]

437
00:21:17,708 --> 00:21:20,166
[chattering excitedly]

438
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,458
[grunts happily]

439
00:21:32,583 --> 00:21:36,458
[water hissing]

440
00:21:36,541 --> 00:21:38,041
Hit it, George!

441
00:21:38,125 --> 00:21:41,125
[chattering in exertion]

442
00:21:45,083 --> 00:21:46,666
[grunts uncomprehendingly]

443
00:21:46,750 --> 00:21:48,500
Let's switch places.

444
00:21:48,583 --> 00:21:50,416
[grunts in agreement]

445
00:21:52,166 --> 00:21:54,541
Here we go!

446
00:21:54,625 --> 00:21:57,541
[panting]

447
00:21:57,625 --> 00:21:59,083
[shimmering tone]

448
00:21:59,166 --> 00:22:02,791
[upbeat music]

449
00:22:02,875 --> 00:22:04,541
Is it working?

450
00:22:04,625 --> 00:22:08,000
[chattering happily]

451
00:22:08,083 --> 00:22:11,125
[laughs]
Great going, guys!

452
00:22:12,708 --> 00:22:17,125
[narrator] <i>Before long,</i>
<i>the ice was nice and smooth.</i>

453
00:22:20,208 --> 00:22:23,458
[shimmering tone]

454
00:22:26,708 --> 00:22:28,666
All set for your first game?

455
00:22:28,750 --> 00:22:31,041
[chatters agreeably]

456
00:22:31,125 --> 00:22:35,458
Here it comes!
[grunts]

457
00:22:36,291 --> 00:22:40,041
[chatters frightfully]

458
00:22:40,125 --> 00:22:41,666
[grunts negatively]

459
00:22:41,750 --> 00:22:44,000
-[chatters happily]
-[laughs]

460
00:22:44,083 --> 00:22:46,041
Just have to work
on the form a little.

461
00:22:46,125 --> 00:22:49,041
-[grunts in agreement]
-[man in yellow hat] Hey, George!

462
00:22:49,125 --> 00:22:52,041
Got room for one more?

463
00:22:52,125 --> 00:22:53,833
-Yeah!
-[chatters excitedly]

464
00:22:53,916 --> 00:22:55,583
[laughter]

465
00:22:56,583 --> 00:22:57,916
[Man in the Yellow Hat
laughing]

466
00:22:58,000 --> 00:22:59,875
[Bill] Nice one, George!

467
00:22:59,958 --> 00:23:02,208
[giggling]

468
00:23:03,250 --> 00:23:06,208
[fast swing music]

469
00:23:06,291 --> 00:23:10,291
<i>♪♪</i>

